OL,3,C'It was a really joyous day': Peter
OL,4,CBott's SS Vega memories 80 years on
OL,6,F"If we had a little drop of soup or
OL,7,Fperhaps a few bones, they would be
OL,8,Frushed back to my mother and my mother
OL,9,Fwould try and make something with what
OL,10,Fwe had."
OL,12,FTowards the end of the war, the
OL,13,Faverage Channel Islander consumed as
OL,14,Flittle as 900 calories a day.
OL,16,FPeter describes: "You were desperate
OL,17,Fto get food and you just ate what you
OL,18,Fcould to keep going but it's very
OL,19,Fdifficult to say what you actually
OL,20,Ffelt like.
